{"word":"ἄφωνος","slug":"ἄφωνος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἄφωνος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:φωνή'><el>φωνή</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>voiceless, speechless, dumb, silent</i>, <b><a href='S:Theognis'>Theogn.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b>: <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <el>ἄφωνος ἀρᾶς</el> <i>unable to utter</i> a curse, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>-νως</el>, <i>without speaking</i>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b>; <a href='S:neuter'>neut.</a> <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> as <a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><el>ἄφωνα</el> (<a href='S:scilicet'>sc.</a> <el>γράμματα</el>), <i>consonants</i>, <a href='S:opposed to'>opp. to</a> <el>φωνοῦντα</el> or <el>φωνήεντα</el> (vowels), <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}